<br>
Pyrocuror = 111/tick<br>
Envenomed Bolt = 162/tick<br>
Cessation of Corr/Splurt = 100/tick<br>
Vexing Mordania = 122/tick<br>
Plague = 58/tick (Yeah, sucky)<br>
Devouring Darkness = 123/tick<br>
Funeral Pyre = 240/tick<br>
Chilling Embrace = 40/tick (yeah, another lame one)<br>
<br>
A necromancer, by the above figures, is not pet dependant. Comparing the DPS of the lame ass (even FOCUSSED) spectre pet compared to the necromancer's DPS isn't even worth it. BTW, a necromancer can stack all of these DoTs on you. At once. The pet hits for maybe high 60s, and misses a lot. Does have a nasty 100 point LTap.<br>
<br>
BLs are MORE pet dependant. They CANNOT DoT like this. Nor should they. They DoT like a lower powered Shaman, although Venom of the Snake is an evil DoT that 34th necromancers love. Therefore, for balance, their pure melee ability, and their pets especially, need a bump. OK, they can tank better than a necromancer, but a necromancer can FD, Harmshield (invulnerability for 18 seconds), gate, self evac and all that stuff, while a BL cannot.<br>
<br>
Mages are also pet dependant, and they also cannot tank, but they do have Gate (and that's ALL their get out of death cards.) Their pet is mostly their defence, their nukes are OK, but not a wizards, and disturbingly, druids are catching up with them [<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ]. I wouldn't feel right having my Lil Snapper able to eat a mage pet one on one. I'd like to have that myself and my pet could at least tear to bits the necro pet and said necro before his DoTs slowly killed us (and they would), or at least give the necro a run for his money. Not it being a no contest on either side.<br>
<br>
I have a necromancer, and I believe that BL pets need an upgrade, because necromancer pets are crap, but it seems that BL pets are LESS than necromancer pets. Necromancers are the Kings and Queens of DoTs, and no one should take that away from them. They can live with being 2nd or 3rd on pets.<br>
<br>
