<br>
This means that one group of necromancers, by my above calculations, not even using all DoTs ... will be doing approximately 2K/tick<br>
<br>
Vex = 122/tick<br>
Pyro = 111/tick<br>
Splurt = 100/tick.<br>
<br>
This is 333/tick. x6 necromancers, this is close to 2K/tick. For some mobs like Thought Horror Overfiend, this will mean the fights are much, much quicker.<br>
<br>
A shaman has 2-3 DoTlines that stack. Two necromancers already have, the Scourge/Plague line and the Venom of the Snake/Envenomed Bolt line.<br>
<br>
A shaman's greatest power is debuffing and buffing. Slow = fantastic. Stat buffs = no one can compare. Toss in regen and Focus, and you've got some very sweet buffs. DoTs are definitely a sideline for shamans, although I'd say they are pretty much number 2. As it stands, normal storebought spells shamans are at least second with DoTs. If you include uber drops, necromancers still lead the way with Funeral Pyre, which is 240/tick.<br>
<br>
(above DoTs mentioned are mostly storebought, Splurt being a drop. CoC will do in a pinch, same damage as Splurt, just less mana efficient.)<br>
<br>
Anyway, this is off topic. Raiding is a completely different situation. Most times, pets aren't even allowed on raids, for fear of pathing bugs and control over them. Yes, they can still break mez, unfortunately <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
